# 10th Exercise

## Estimate the costs of this project and explain your rationale. For which price would you sell your software for? Explain why.


Development Costs

AR Developer : 50.000€ - 60.000€ -> Specialized AR devs charge 50€-100€/hr
Game Developer: 10.000€ - 20.000€ -> Core gameplay + networking
UI/UX Designer: 5.000€ - 10.000€ -> AR interfaces require intuitive design
Backend: $15,000€ - 20.000€
Project Management: round about 30.000€ -> Jira
Total Development Cost 110.000€ - $145.000€ for 2 months


Additional Costs

AR Glasses Testing : 2.000€ - 5.000€ -> Need multiple devices (Meta Quest, HoloLens, etc.)
Beta Testing: 3.000€ - 7.000€ -> External testers & debugging
App Store Fees (Google Play, Apple): 100€ - 300€/year -> One-time developer fees
Marketing (Ads, Social Media, Influencers): 5.000€ - 10.000 -> Depends on reach
Legal (Terms, Privacy Policy, Copyright): 5.000€ - 10.000€ -> Lawyer fees for compliance
Total Additional Costs 20.000€ - 30,000€


Ongoing Costs (Yearly)

Server Costs -> 1.000€ - 5.000€/year
Maintenance (Updates, Bug Fixes) -> 5.000€ - 15.000€/year
Marketing -> 5.000€ - 10.000€/year
Low-End Estimate: ~11.000€


I would sell this software app on the app store as freemium but only the basic options would not cost anything for the customer.
Hence I would also upgrade the option to a monthly and yearly subscription. 10€/month and 100€/year

For testing, I would use the 2× Quest 3, plus a HoloLens which will be like 6.000€







